Alchoholics Anonymous | Pacific and Grays Harbor County

Welcome to District 21

District 21 is comprised of AA Groups in and around the Grays Harbor and Pacific County coastal region. We are glad you’re here. The purpose of this site is to make sure you can find your way to a meeting within our district, or guide you to the helping hand of AA close to you.

AA’s Preamble

Alcoholics Anonymous is a fellowship of men and women who share their experience, strength and hope with each other that they may solve their common problem and help others to recover from alcoholism. The only requirement for membership is a desire to stop drinking.

Used with Permission – AA Grapevine, Inc.
About AA

Alcoholics Anonymous is not affiliated with any other organization, although many have adapted A.A.’s Twelve Steps for their own use. A.A. is self-supporting, declining outside contributions; and we are non-professional, offering only the voluntary support of one alcoholic helping another. Anonymity lies at the heart of our Fellowship and strives to insure members that their recovery will be private.

A Service to you

This website contains information about the AA meetings and recovery related events in District 21. We hope that you find the information accurate and helpful. We welcome your comments and suggestions. For suggestions or additional content requests, please contact the District 21 Webmaster.
